caption: Best kept secret on Barracks Row.
This is the Only sushi place worth going to in a mile radius.
So delicious and the staff is so polite and friendly!
This is my go-to sushi place. Affordable, delicious, and generous portions. I'm a big fan of the sunset roll!
Always great sushi!!!!
My favorite sushi place in DC!!!! Friendly staff and amazing food!
The best sushi in SE and NE.
Excellent service and food in the middle of covid
Amazing sushi and very nice family run business

I’d been to Torai Sushi once prior to COVID, but once we started getting takeout from them in the age of social distancing, we were blown away.  Ordering online is extremely easy and the time estimate they provide you is actually accurate. Whenever we’ve ordered from them, they’re super quick - no longer than 20-25 minutes.  I will recommend doing takeout from them (whether we are in a pandemic or not). They are definitely a hole-in-the-wall spot and don’t have a ton of seating inside, so don’t go with a big group.  Usually when we order from them, we’re in a sushi rut and go wild ordering 7-9 rolls at a time for the three of us, and they display them so nicely on a tray every time.  The rolls are great for the price and we appreciate the time and effort they take in making our sushi beautifully displayed - it’s like we got catering for our own little sushi night.  Definitely check this spot out!
Amazing fresh sushi. My favorite sushi place in DC.
This spot is worth visiting. They have large portions for fair prices. Constantly well organized and with excellent vibes. Will come back again.

California roll 72 pc. Worth the 50.00$ loved it so much the freash food is amassing and tasting so good. The presentation is drop dead gorgeous and one I find 5 star restaurant I love this one and will come back. That from a truck driver. So if you have time come here worth every penny!!
Excellent sushi, very friendly staff, felt very covid safe
Great sushi and ramen, friendly service.
Call in orders typically ready in 15 minutes. Friendly service and quality sushi.

First time ordering lunch from here (during COVID so had to do takeout) and I must say, this is the yummiest sushi I've had in a while. It's obvious that they use high quality ingredients and that they put a lot of love into their preparation.  I eat a plant-based diet so I ordered a veggie tempura appetizer. A standard vegetable roll (asparagus, cucumber, avocado) and a tempura vegetable roll and OMG all the veggies were super fresh and crisp and just delicious, and they don't skimp out on the good stuff either and put tons of rice and less of the other stuff like a lot of sushi joints do! These were legit, dense, hearty sushi rolls!  I asked for extra sauce and apparently they usually charge for extra but because I'd already paid with a card, she let it slide. However I would have no problem paying extra seeing as if I paid less than $25 for the entire meal (couldn't even finish all of it because I got full) Super nice folks.  ***There's metered street parking (parallel as well as diagonal parking on the other side of the street) but I kinda cheated and just ran in and got my food and ran back out to my car.***  Great quality, fresh ingredients, superb customer service, inexpensive... I will DEFINITELY be back! 🖤🖤🖤
The customer service is consistently quick, awesome atmosphere, very friendly staff. I will come back again when I am in the area.
cordial staff & delicious sushi.
(Translated by Google) The taste is usually  (Original) 맛은 보통
Such a wonderful, low-key, no frills sushi spot. Fresh fish, small space, friendly and efficient service. They're not trying to earn huge awards, just serving up good food in a casual spot.
Definitely will be back! Got the bibimbap and it was delicious and cheap (especially for DC).

Wonderful food!! Especially the ginger tea which I would drink every day of the world. Wish I would've gotten recipe or name of it. Was in DC for Women's March and since I'm from San Antonio the cold was kicking my butt. The ramen noodles were an excellent balm for my soul. Went back next day and got the Miso instead of the chicken. Only wish the videos playing on t.v. had the sound on instead of radio.
I love this hole in the wall spot. Staff is super friendly. Sushi is top notch. Ramen is dope. Basically it's a must try! 🍣 🍶🍜

"Holy cow" and "oh my goodness" were two of the things I said tonight while we were eating here. It could be just as applicable to the fact that I was unaware this place was even here, but these were my reactions to how good the food was. Delicious sushi and genuinely good Korean dishes in a little hole in the wall on Eighth Street.
I just can't stop going back, the food is great. The yellow tail sushi is still one of the best I have had!
Food is very fresh. Service is phenomenal.
A small restaurant that’s more of a fusion of Japanese and Korean. Food is good and well presented.
Friendly staff. Even though seating is small we always dine in. Very good sushi and sashimi but they also have a Japanese Ramen menu and a Korean bulgogi menu too.

(Translated by Google) It is a good place to eat, the ramen is quite large, if you do not eat much maybe you could use sharing dishes. In general everything is excellent: the service, clean bathrooms (there is only one by the way) and the food very well done.  (Original) Es un buen lugar para comer, el ramen es bastante grande, si no comes mucho quizás te vendría bien compartir platillos. En general todo es excelente: el servicio, baños limpios (solo hay uno por cierto) y la comida muy bien hecha.
Food was good but service was terrible. Extremely slow. Had to keep trying to get their attention and there was no one else in the restaurant.

I went to this place on 12-19-19 I ordered Shrimp Tempura and Eel & Crab Tempura. While the guy was preparing my order a piece of the eel & crab tempura fell on the floor. The guy turned his back behind down and placed the piece back onto the tray and attempted to service it to me. I WILL NEVER EAT THERE AGAIN AND I SUGGEST YOU NOT TO EAT THERE EITHER!!!
We come here at least twice a month. Exceptional quality and very reasonably priced. It’s our favorite sushi place!
Delicious food!

This is the best sushi in DC, plus more delicious options. Super nice staff. Super cute decor. Great to eat in or take out! It's very small, but usually not packed. Definitely give it a try if you're in the area!

Excellent spot for high-quality sushi. The restaurant is casual; you order at the counter and a server brings you your food.  Expect well portioned rolls and fresh fish, tasty appetizers, and friendly staff.
Delicious, humble, courteous! Worth every penny
Their sushi is amazing and very affordable prices!
Unassuming restaurant with a wonderful menu and delicious fresh food. Great customer service.
The best Ramen/sushi place in DC!! The people that work there are so personable and nice! Please go!
My favorite DC sushi place!
I come here at least once a week for lunch. The food is just great! The staff is really friendly too!
Excellent sushi, friendly staff, plain environment.

I really enjoyed myself here today, with my princess. She is fascinated with Asian culture. Her future career in animation will take her to Japan some day. She suggested we come here, so I could broaden my taste buds horizon's. I am so glad I did. The food was amazing. The beverage imported from Japan was tasty. The price for ALL of it was AFFORDABLE and RIGHT!!! I'm not sure if I will ever make it to Japan. However, coming to dine in here DEFINITELY gives me a good glimpse of what it would be like.

The food was extremely well presented in a way where it was definitely crafted like an artpiece. The quality is what you'd expect at this price and they have a good variety of sake I enjoyed. Would go again.

Really enjoyed our meal here.  The rolls were complex and flavorful, the poke bowl was bigger than expected.  The Yellowtail Belly sashimi was the best.  But the part that I will go back for is the intimacy, the handful of small table, the proximity to the chefs and the quiet ambiance that allows a conversation.
Small place with few seats but food is delicious.

Ordered takeout and was skeptical when I first opened everything up. We had a couple of sushi rolls, chicken teriyaki, and ramen. Despite our skepticism of the appearance, everything tasted really good. Sushi was fresh and the spicy rolls were actually spicy! Everything was seasoned well and cooked well. The restaurant itself is very small, so would recommend grabbing it to-go. Definitely worth giving a try!
I ordered the unagi Donburri and enjoyed it. I would definitely recommend to others.
Not perfect service, but the sushi is awesome. Smallish place so snuggle in, have a beer and enjoy your edanami. can't go wrong on what you order so pick your favorite. Enjoy.

I was dining in and was asked to pay for my food first. I'll never go back to this establishment. In spite of being profiled i still gave a tip but it sure left a bad taste on my brain. Happy Veterans Day weekend America.

This is the perfect hole in the wall sushi spot! I was the only tourist in there, which is always a good sign. The seating area is small, but they make the best of it. Nice beverage selection too. Lots of options for sake, Japanese beer, marble sodas, etc.  The food was tasty too. The edamame was a little underdone (they initially forget to bring it out) but had some of the better spicy mayo I’ve ever tasted. The rolls were delicious too. I especially liked the Sunset roll.
Great food!

We have visited this tiny shop in the past and were pleasantly surprised at their upgrade to the "dining" area.  from a few stools and chairs to an intimate feeling nook with seating for maybe 10.  The food is very very good.  be aware that spicy can be spicy.  Our party included a reluctant participant not interested in spicy or raw anything, but was pleased with a "spicy pork" bento box (passed the 3 pieces of california roll to others, but still had a filling meal).  poke bowl looked small, but was filling.  the sushi was made to order by a skilled chef who clearly took pride even in the most elementary requests.  be careful with the parking regulations.  they are clearly posted and marked.
Loved this little sushi place! Wonderful sushi and homey, laid back feel. Highly recommend!
Great service, and quality sushi.
The food is amazing
Personal service and great food.
Cozy spot, friendly service, nice decor
Very good
Really good sushi!! What a little gem. The decor and seating area don't look like much, but wow the sushi! Incredibly fresh and creative rolls.

I absolutely love this place! The fish is some of the freshest I've tasted at a sushi restaurant, with their salmon being my favorite. Another excellent quality about Torai is that its prices are kept quite low when compared to the more Westernized sushi restaurants in the DMV.
The miso soup was the best I've ever had and the sushi was really good. The employees were also very nice. Walking in was a little confusing if you sit and order or go to the counter.  Etc.
I always get the Spicy Miso Ramen, Spider Roll, and Smoked Salmon Sashimi! The food is perfect every time and the staff is super friendly! Hands down my favorite Ramen spot to go to.

Food is decent, but they have inexplicably long cooking times that can really ruin your plans. Have ordered here and been told food would be ready in 10 minutes, and it ended up taking 35 minutes with no explanation or apology. Nobody's got time for that kind of nonsense.
Great little spot across from Marine Barracks. It's small, and cozy with terrific food.

Amazing local small spot for sushi, and other Japanese dishes. The physical restaurant is small and there is not a lot of space for seating, but most orders are take out so it is not too big of a deal. As soon as you walk in you can smell the food, as the kitchen is open air and right there. Its a quick walk right to the register to either order or pick up. We had a spice salmon hand roll that was delicious, a specialty tuna roll, and the dumplings. It was all excellent and we will definitely be going back.
Good quality and good value sushi. Sampling of plates from around Asia if you want something other than sushi, too.
Amazing ramen when my lady was sick.  And the sushi 🍣 was fresh  Also, the service was quite friendly.
Small shop, decent food. Friendly service.
Really great little sushi restaurant!! Sushi is reasonably priced, and very tasty. Also had the bulgogi bibimbap which was delicious! Also the Kpop that they play on the TV is unique, and so fun!
We got takeout for our anniversary. It was delicious. Would absolutely order here again.
Took my son who was visiting from out of town here and he really liked it.  Small place but good food.
Okay if you need a Korean fix.

Better than Nobu dc, Hamilton, and SEI. The only spot in DC I don’t leave disappointed and missing California sushi. Very small place, with minimal table service, but flippin’ delicious and reasonably priced. Plus next door to the best donut in the city if you’ve got a sweet tooth.

I put Torai in the running for best sushi in the city. They serve very fresh fish and their sushi is made with care. This is a small business and the owners are always around and extremely friendly. Have never had a bad experience with anything on the menu and would highly recommend.
Great little hole in the wall.
One of my favorite sushi joints.  Very small and welcoming.

I was very excited about the place since all the reviews are good. Yet I was very disappointed. The few rolls and sashimi pieces are not fresh and some very obviously old. The tuna was simply dry and that take a number of laying around to get to that state.  Another thing that was kind of shocking is that when I asked for a glass of water they told me, they do not have any and I have to buy a bottled one, which is fine financially, but I have never been refused a glass of water (even in Paris!)  The service was also very bad. Every time I had to get up and go get someone. First it was to take my order, then to remind about other things we have ordered and at the end they actually forgot one. The I had to get up and find someone to ask for the check and then the same thing to actually pay. We had a table and we actually had to get up and go to the bar to pick our orders ourselves. There were 4 of us, so it was quite a few times. If I wanted that type of service, I would have sat by the bar!

Really delicious and fresh. I think I was expecting the specialty roll's fish to be cooked or seared (it was a wide variation of fish) but it still ended up being delicious. I'm glad I know they're there now! 🖤
Delicious sushi and ramen. Friendly service! Only complaint is they give you a flimsy plastic disposable spoon to eat ramen with.

Really LOVE this place.  Very small and mom and popish but the sushi is top notch.  Best chirashi I have had yet in DC, lots of fish, veggies and perfectly spicy.  Without the rice,  it would be a wonderful keto bowl.  And the fish 4 ways (sushi, sashimi, 1 cut and 1 handroll) of the fish of your choice for under $20 is a serious deal.

This place is a tucked away treasure. I’ve had ramen soup in several locations across the country, including abroad in Japan, and this is as authentic as it gets. The soup was hearty and packed with amazing flavors. I could taste the cook took hours to make the broth. I ordered the spicy ramen, and it was cooked to perfection to include the soft boiled egg and pork belly. Mmmmm. The spicy dragon roll was great with what I thought was eel to top it off for some crispy texture. This is has become a DC favorite since moving here 5 months ago.
Best sushi I've ever had.... they treat me like family!
Owner's were very friendly with great services and sushi & soup was fantastic and price was affordable for the very delicious  gourmet food.......
Bulgogi Bimbimbap with miso soup was delicious! 👌😋 Must visit again!
Wonderful little spot with really nice owners. The sushi is great for the price. There is better sushi in the area like Capitol Sushi but for the price you really can’t beat it.

Great service and delicious fresh sushi. We have been here several times and are greeted as family... Sushi chef will make a special treat for us each time. They remember and acknowledge you as a returned customer. This is a big reason we return. Try the Sake!!!
Good sushi and quick service in Capitol Hill South or Navy yard area.
I ordered the Dupbap Spicy Pork which was AMAZING. The service was quick and hostess was very kind. Definitely coming back for more.
Great quality, especially given the affordable prices.
Excellent sushi at a great value prepared by friendly staff!

Food was delicious, got the Torai, Vegas, and Philly rolls and the taste and presentation was fantastic. Service was incredibly warm and friendly and quite speedy. Be aware that it is a small (cozy) space but the music and overall atmosphere makes it a great place to eat. Highly recommend to anyone looking for good sushi.
Good fresh sushi, with delicious gyoza and miso soup. We got the daily special on a Saturday. Food was quickly served with great service!!!
Amazing food.  Friendly staff.  They gave us complimentary sweet potato noodles.  The pieces of salmon it the sushi were great. Prices very reasonable. Amazing place.
I love everything about Torai. It has great sushi, poke bowls, and bibimbap. The staff are all super nice, and the place is really cozy.
Stellar place for poke bowls, sushi, bibimbap, and more. The place is cozy, and the staff are all incredibly friendly. I never pass up the opportunity to stop in when I’m in the area.
I rate a restaurant based on whether or not I need to bring my umami shaker with me. torai sushi has all the umami, no more needed.
Great food, wonderful fast service, you can't go wrong with anything on the menu.

Very tasty chicken bento box for take out ($12).  Warm welcoming people and atmosphere.  And lovely fresh food, several interesting menu choices at good prices.  Only open until 8 pm but that will change to 9 pm in a few weeks.
Amazing people, amazing sushi. Very well run! Expect the best every time.
I really love this place. Great food. Pretty comfy inside.
Great food
Excellent hidden gem of a sushi place. Fast friendly service and great food.
Fantastic place to come grab a poke bowl, sushi, or various Korean foods. Delicious and affordable. I will be coming here often!
Very nice people and amazing sushi!
Amazing food. Great prices. Will definitely be returning

Teriyaki bento was so good! Service was great and food came out fast. The owner is korean and was so incredibly nice. I lived in Korea for 4 months and miss it dearly! The owner gave me some homemade cucumber kimchi because I was telling him how much I missed it! Made my week and I will definitely be going back ^.^
It was so awesome places to have lunch!!!   Food was so so GOOD!!!!  NEVER fail to get satisfaction!!^^
Nice to have in the neighborhood, would not make it a destination meal.

I did not try the sushi this time, but the ramen and bulgogi bibimbap are really good. The broth was a bit salty, but the flavor more than made up for it. There was a generous helping of pork chashu, and some fresh bokchoy in the mix. Best of all, the staff is super friendly. I'll be back!

Amazing sushi and ramen!! The staff is very courteous and friendly, and food is worth going back again and again. This place is the best kept secret in Capitol Hill, unassuming if not easy to miss from outside yet a culinary delight once you journey your way through the eclectic menu. The sushi is on par with any overpriced sushi house in NY and the ramen is some of the best around including any in No Va or Montgomery County.

Large Japanese/Korean menu.  Sushi, poke bowls, bibimbap, etc. Super friendly service, not crowded, so far.  Very reasonable prices, open for lunch (and breakfast on weekends!). I had the chirashi sushi.  Lots of fresh fish.  Could easily sell for $25, but they charge $15! I expect to be there often.
Korean and Japanese place with unique dishes hard to find at other places, like hwedubap (Korean style chopped fish over rice with spicy sauce).
